description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is currently a unique and exciting vacancy within the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Berkshire NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; which will allow the successful candidate to gain &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;regular shifts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and valuable &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;. This is a fantastic opportunity for a talented Senior Mental Health Nurse who shares the Trusts’ vision to be on the leading edge of healthcare for the benefit of their patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will be providing support to the Child and Adolescent Mental Health Service, with a specific focus on Eating Disorders. Berkshire Eating Disorders Service - Children, Young People and Families (BEDS - CYPF) – is a community based specialist service supporting children and young people who have an Eating Disorder. The Eating Disorders service works with young people aged 8-18 providing assessment and treatment to young people and their families who have anorexia nervosa, bulimia nervosa, binge eating disorder or atypical eating disorder.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locations covered: &lt;/strong&gt;Nicholsons House, Maidenhead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Length of placement:&lt;/strong&gt; 6 months, subject to review&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 – Example Rate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Day Rate - £20.35 per hour&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Night/Sat Rate - £26.16 per hour&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sun/Bank Holiday Rate - £31.97 per hour&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The responsibilities of the post-holder are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To work effectively individually and as part of a multi-disciplinary team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To develop and maintain specialist knowledge of child protection issues and the Mental Health Act, as they would relate to young people referred to this service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To have knowledge of the capacity act and Gillick Competency principles in relation to consent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be responsible for the care of assigned patients and to manage, direct and evaluate their care in an effective manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be able to communicate effectively with other professionals about issues relating to patients’ care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To communicate complex information to young people and families&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To escalate as required, reporting any incidents/accidents and ensuring they are recorded using the appropriate method&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to apply for a post you &lt;strong&gt;must&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a registered Mental Health Nurse (Part 3/8/13 of the UKCC Register) or possess a relevant post graduate qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience of working within a mental health setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess the ability to take responsibility for inpatient activity and day care through managing and co-ordinating &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to work effectively as part of a team and in a high-pressure environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to evidence continuing professional development and a desire to undertake further training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work and your professional, caring and reliable service you will have access to the following benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive, weekly pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to the NHSP Stakeholder Pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid annual leave and statutory maternity pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training and development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registration with NHS Professionals is subject to employment history and reference checking and offers of registration are therefore conditional upon the receipt of satisfactory references&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
